      "text": "Failure meant shame and rejection. Failure was to be avoided at all cost. Students knew this. It was the fear of failure that created obedience.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "0ff44a38454af1f8",
      "text": "But in this agile learning paradigm, you have to fail. Failure is how we learn. For each time we fail, previously unrecognized false assumptions are illuminated. We [[Know the Problem]] better. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "04708be1adf4fc16",
      "text": "We try again, this time emboldened with deeper understanding. We may not know what is true, but we now know what is not true. We are incrementally smarter with each progressive cycle. Do those cycles fast and we learn fast.\n"
    },
    {
